        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-08T16:10:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1. extern \"C\" to clarify? (Even though the system header should already be providing that.)\n\n2. Do you want __attribute__((visibility(\"default\")))? (I think that it’s so weird that ELF symbols bind solely by name and not by library, making it possible to do runtime interposition in this way, so it’s not necessarily what I would have had in mind. Ought to be fine to have users request this behavior by linking this library explicitly. But you may have had the forced interposition thing in mind, so I’m asking.)",
      "revId": "361dc6356c54c36f8395aafcb189d69783a8c431",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
